Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language): The paper focuses on speech recognition and language processing, which falls under this category. 
- cs.SD (Sound): The paper deals with acoustic models for speech recognition, which is related to sound processing. 
- cs.SI (Signal Processing): The paper involves processing of speech signals, which is a subfield of signal processing. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes a new end-to-end speech recognition model, which involves machine learning techniques. 
- cs.SD (Speech Recognition): The paper is primarily focused on improving speech recognition models, which is a subfield of speech processing.
